# Keeping DEVELOPMENT.md Current

DEVELOPMENT.md is the project memory. Update it proactively — not just at session end — whenever any of the following happen:

## Update immediately when:

- A bug is found (add to "Bugs found and fixed" with full explanation of what was wrong, why it was dangerous, and what the fix was)
- A bug is fixed (confirm it's documented with enough detail that a future agent won't re-introduce it)
- An architecture decision is made or changed (add reasoning — the "why" matters more than the "what")
- A known gap is resolved (move it out of the gaps section and into the session log)
- A new known gap is discovered (add it to the gaps section immediately)
- A design discussion produces a conclusion (e.g. user agrees on an approach — capture it)
- A file is created, significantly changed, or deleted (update the file map and status)
- A phase of the roadmap is completed or started
- Any understanding is reached that a new context would need to do good work

## What good documentation looks like:

- Bugs: what was wrong, what incorrect behavior it caused, why it was dangerous, the exact fix
- Decisions: the options considered, the reasoning for the choice made, what would invalidate it
- Gaps: specific description of the problem, why it's not fixed yet, what to do when fixing it
- Rationale: enough context that someone who wasn't in the conversation understands why

## What not to do:

- Do not summarize or compress. Detail is the point.
- Do not omit reasoning to save space. The "why" is more valuable than the "what."
- Do not defer updates to "the end of the session." Context may be lost before then.
- Do not add session log entries for trivial changes (formatting fixes, typo corrections).
